TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chambers, David
AU  - Sarkissian, Sergei
AU  - Schill, Michael J
T1  - Market and Regional Segmentation and Risk Premia in the First Era of Financial Globalization
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx143
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 10
SP  - 4063
EP  - 4098
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study market segmentation effects using data on U.S. railroads that list their bonds in New York and London between 1873 and 1913. This sample provides a unique setting for such analysis because of the precision offered by bond yields in cost of capital estimation, the geography-specific nature of railroad assets, and ongoing substantial technological change. We document a significant reduction in market segmentation over time. While New York bond yields exceeded those in London in the 1870s, this premium disappeared by the early 1900s. However, the segmentation premium persisted in the more remote regions of the United States.Received June 18, 2015; editorial decision October 4, 2017 by Editor Robin Greenwood.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx143
ER  - 



